latestPosts.caption:
There’s a fire that doesn’t roar, it smolders.
Silent, deep, unforgettable.❤️

“Vanilla on Fire” is that slow burn.
A rich, intoxicating blend where creamy vanilla meets smoky woods and embered spice;
not sweet, but bold. Not loud, but lingering.
It wraps around the senses like a memory you didn’t know you still felt.💌

For the nights that speak in glances,
and the souls that set sparks in silence.🫶🏻

latestPosts.caption:
It began with a glance…
That fleeting moment when time slowed, words fumbled, and the world fell silent except for the flutter within.☺️

“Butterflies in My Stomach” is that feeling, bottled.
A soft, playful scent that captures the innocence of first love, the thrill of anticipation, the magic of maybe.
Crafted with tender florals and a whisper of warmth, it lingers like the memory of a smile.🫶🏻

“To the man who gave me my safest place,
You may not have always said the words,
But your silence held my storms.
Your steady presence made the world feel less loud.
Because of you, I slept carefree,
Dreamed freely,
Laughed without fear.

My quiet strength in the chaos.

Today and always, I celebrate you.
Your love. Your grace. Your scent, just like your love;
Unseen, but always felt.

Happy Father’s Day”❤️
